                    breaking down the usage into different groups/tenants. Each definition describes a breakdown that will be
                    added as additional one to the breakdowns provided explicitly in the JSON payloads.
                    Defaults to null value which means no additional breakdown is computed.
                  items:
                    description: Pivot definition which will be used for breaking down the usage into different groups/tenants.
                    properties:
                      breakdownBy:
                        description: Type of the breakdown groups/tenants provided by the pivot definition.
                        type: object
                        x-kubernetes-preserve-unknown-fields: true
                      groupBy:
                        description: |-
                          Array of the attributes from the JSON payload to use as a (potentially multidimensional)
                          grouping key that represents the breakdown group/tenant.
                        items:
                          description: |-
                            Attribute from the JSON payload that takes part in constituting a (potentially multidimensional) grouping key
                            that represents the breakdown group/tenant.
                          pattern: ^.{1,255}$
                          type: string
                        type: array
                      processing:
                        description: |-
                          Optional aggregation processing within the same breakdown group/tenant represented by the specific
                          breakdown group/tenant. If processing is 'COUNT', then it means that the number of JSON payloads
                          is counted for each grouping key (payloads with the same values for the grouping key will be grouped
                          together and the amount of those payloads will be reported as the key's breakdown value). If processing is 'ADD',
                          then it means that the values reported in the attribute specified in the source field of JSON payloads
                          will be added up for each grouping key (payloads with the same values for the grouping key will be
                          grouped together and the sum of the values of attribute specified in the source field will be
                          reported as the key's breakdown value). If processing is 'MAX', then it means that the greatest value reported
                          in the attribute specified in the source field of JSON payloads will be set for each grouping key
                          (payloads with the same values for the grouping key will be grouped together and the greatest value will be reported
                          as the key's breakdown value). If processing is 'LAST', then it means that the latest received value from
                          values reported in the attribute specified in the source field of JSON payloads will be set for each grouping key
                          (payloads with the same values for the grouping key will be grouped together and the value that was
                          received later will be reported as the key's breakdown value). Defaults to processing selected in data section.
                        type: string
                      source:
                        description: |-
                          Attribute from the JSON payload that is being aggregated based on the grouping key that
                          represents the breakdown group/tenant - this field is required if value of processing field is other than 'COUNT'.
                        pattern: ^.{1,255}$
                        type: string
                    required:
